Build a Django web app for a family diet and exercise tracker.

Goal:
A private family web app where each family member can log meals, exercise, body weight, water intake, and ask an AI assistant for general wellness suggestions.

Tech stack:
- Django
- PostgreSQL preferred, SQLite acceptable for local dev
- Bootstrap 5 UI
- OpenAI API integration using the Responses API
- Environment variables for secrets
- Ready for deployment on Render/Railway

Core requirements:
1. User authentication
   - Login/logout/register
   - Each user belongs to a Family
   - Each user has a profile: name, age, gender, height, weight, goal, dietary preference, medical notes optional

2. Meal tracking
   - Add meal log: date, meal type, food description, estimated calories, protein, notes
   - List today’s meals
   - Weekly meal history

3. Exercise tracking
   - Add exercise: date, type, duration, intensity, notes
   - Weekly exercise summary

4. Body tracking
   - Weight log
   - Water intake log
   - Simple dashboard with today and weekly summary

5. AI assistant
   - Chat page
   - User can ask diet/exercise questions
   - Backend should fetch only that user’s recent 7 days meal/exercise/weight summary
   - Send that summary to OpenAI
   - AI must provide general wellness suggestions only, not medical diagnosis
   - Add disclaimer in responses
   - Store chat history

6. Safety
   - Do not expose OPENAI_API_KEY in frontend
   - All OpenAI calls must happen from Django backend
   - Users can only see their own logs
   - Add basic validation

7. Pages:
   - Home dashboard
   - Register/login
   - Profile page
   - Add meal
   - Add exercise
   - Add weight/water
   - History page
   - AI assistant chat page

8. Deliverables:
   - Complete Django project structure
   - requirements.txt
   - .env.example
   - README.md with local setup steps
   - Render deployment notes
   - Clean Bootstrap UI
   - Django admin enabled

Use clean readable code with comments. Make this an MVP, not overcomplicated.

Also I have deepseek API key